comment: RATR shows that Griffin (LAC) makes incidental contact and does not push Curry (GSW) away from the ball.
After Thompson (GSW) sets a legal screen, Griffin (LAC) and Curry (GSW) make incidental foot to foot contact that causes Griffin to trip to the floor.
Jordan (LAC) cleanly strips the ball from Green (GSW).
LATR shows that Griffin (LAC) maintains legal guarding position and cleanly strips the ball from Curry (GSW).
Barnes (GSW) sets the screen on Paul (LAC) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court of simultaneous touching prior to the ball going OOB was overturned and Golden State was awarded possession.
Barnes (GSW) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Paul's (LAC) driving shot attempt.
Jordan (LAC) makes contact with Curry's (GSW) head and body that affects his layup attempt.

Green (GSW) momentarily touches Pierce's (LAC) side with his left hand but does not affect his RSBQ on the drive. He then keeps an extended forearm in contact with Pierce, but it is below FT line extended and does not affect his shot attempt.
RHH shows that after Green (GSW) makes contact with the ball, Barnes (GSW) makes contact with Pierce's (LAC) body that affects his shot attempt.
Griffin (LAC) commits a take foul on Curry (GSW).
Paul (LAC) delivers contact to Green (GSW) on the screen and does not give him room to avoid the contact.

After communicating with the Replay Center, the oncourt ruling that Griffin (LAC) stepped out-of-bounds by touching the boundary line while in possession of the ball stood because there was no conclusive angle to show that his foot was inbounds.
Crawford (LAC) commits a take foul on Thompson (GSW).
